ch regulatory requirements,  laws,  and University policies through education, review and quality improvement activities.   The collaborative mission of these units is to facilitate and foster the highest ethical standards in the conduct of research.          compliance        Human Subject Protections          Embryonic Stem Cell Review Committee          Animal Care and Use          Recombinant DNA and Biohazards          Export Controls          Conflict of Interest          Environmental Health and Safety Office          Research Integrity          Ethics          Clinical Studies Coverage Analysis              Compliance    Back to main content           Human Subjects Research (IRB)     Getting Started     OPRS Live Electronic Protocol Submission System    Investigator Responsibilities    Forms & Templates    Submission Deadlines & Meeting Dates      Investigator Training    OPRS Live Electronic Protocol Submission System    Forms & Templates    Policies    External IRBs     Reliance Agreements    Western IRB (WIRB)    Single IRB Review/Reliance    National Cancer Institute (NCI) Central IRB (CIRB)    Chicago Area IRB (CHAIRb)      General Information     UIC Collaborative Units    Board Composition & Expertise    Compliance with HHS & FDA    Online Resources    IRB Fees    Top Tips      Quality Assurance Program (QAP)     Policy    Education & Training    Resources      Reporting Human Subject Concerns    Contact Us      Animal Care & Use (ACC)     ACC Meeting & Deadlines    Committee Composition & Expertise    ACC Forms    Policies & Guidelines    ACC Education & Training     Accessing ACC Online Training Instructions      FAQs     General Protocol Submission & Getting Started    Completing Protocols    Protocol-Funding Matches      Reporting Animal Concerns    Adoption Policy    Contact Us      rDNA & Infectious Agents (IBC)     Forms    Committee Composition & Expertise    Meeting & Deadlines    Policies & Guidelines    Education & Training    Online Resou